The paper presents a new online learning algorithm for collaborative filtering, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of recommender systems. The algorithm is based on a novel approach that combines random playout and randomized rounding of loss subgradients, which is likely to be of interest to researchers in the field of machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the link between batch learning and transductive online learning, which could be of interest to researchers in the field of information theory (cs.IT) and social networks (cs.SI).
